                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.203/201: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-23T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 23, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1653. The viewpoint expressed in the last sentence of section 2 of your no. 2177
                    of December 12, 6 p.m., has been discussed informally with the War Department,
                    which states that it appreciates the necessity for exemplary conduct on the part
                    of its personnel and that <pb facs="0107" n="95" xml:id="pg_95"/> American
                    troops in Egypt are under standing instructions with respect thereto.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
